IN THE COURT OF APPEALS OF THE NAVAJO NATION WINDOW ROCK, ARIZONA THE NAVAJO TRIBE OF INDIANS, Range and Livestock Department, Petitioner, vs. TEDDY CHICO, C#59236 c/o Toh-la-kai Trading Post Gallup, New Mexico, Bobby Rico, C#88512 Twin Lakes, New Mexico Claimants.

NO.

Dated this 28th day of November, 1979.

The Court having reviewed Claimant/Appellee, Teddy Chico's Motion to Deny Appeal and finding good cause therefore, IT IS ORDERED that the above-captioned matter is hereby DISMISSED on the grounds that Claimant/Appellant Bobby Rico failed to file a Motion for Reconsideration with the District Court pursuant to Rule 5(d) of the Navajo Court Rules of Appellate Procedure.

Jerome McCabe Acting Chief Justice of the Navajo Nation
